
## C‑rep: Carbon Emissions Reporting Platform


Frist of all main task is calcuating carbon. This is a professional, modern, good looking software.

C‑rep helps organizations track, calculate, and report their carbon footprint across projects, activities, and evidence. It’s multi‑tenant, secure by design (RLS), and optimized for a clean UX with responsive, sustainable theming.

### Core Objectives
- Record emissions entries (energy, transport, materials)
- Organize by projects and members (owner/editor/viewer roles)
- Attach evidence files (images, PDFs) with secure storage
- Generate basic reports and exports (CSV, printable)
- Multi‑language (TR/EN) with instant switching
- Strong security: Supabase Auth + Postgres RLS

### Primary Users
- Organization owner/admin
- Project managers
- Contributors (data entry)
- Viewers/auditors (read‑only)

---

## Tech Stack and Architecture

### Languages
- TypeScript everywhere (frontend + server actions)
- SQL for database migrations

### Frontend
- Next.js 15 (App Router, React Server Components)
- React 19
- Tailwind CSS v4 (utility‑first)
- Lucide icons, also can be others too
- Radix UI Dialog for accessible modals
- Class Variance Authority (CVA) for component variants
- clsx + tailwind‑merge for class utilities

### Backend
- Supabase:
  - Auth (email/password or magic link)
  - Postgres (schema, policies)
  - Storage (evidence bucket)
  - SSR helpers for cookie‑based sessions

### Security and Auth
- Supabase Auth with cookie session via @supabase/ssr
- Postgres RLS (Row Level Security)
- SECURITY DEFINER functions for non‑recursive inserts
- Owner shortcuts in policies for admin actions
- Minimal attack surface: uploads via storage policies

### Internationalization
- Cookie‑based locale (tr/en)
- Server‑side t() using messages dictionary
- Client LangSwitcher posts to a server action

### Styling and Theme
- Sustainable theme: emerald/green palette
- Glassmorphism accents
- Responsive layouts
- System fonts or Google fonts (Geist)

### Data Model (Core Tables)
- projects (id, name, description, owner_id, created_at)
- project_members (project_id, user_id, role: owner/editor/viewer)
- entries (id, project_id, type, amount, unit, date, notes)
- evidence_files (id, project_id, entry_id?, file_path, mime, hash, size)
- audit_logs (id, user_id, action, resource, metadata, created_at)

### High‑Level Architecture
- Next.js app router provides UI and server actions
- Supabase SSR client in server components
- RLS ensures tenants can only access their own data
- Storage policies check project membership/ownership
- Evidence uploads: client computes SHA‑256 and records metadata

