## Step 4: Supabase Setup

1. Create a project in Supabase, copy:
   - NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL
   - NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY
2. Add to `.env.local`:
   - NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL=...
   - NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=...
3. Database schema migrations under db/migrations (runnable in SQL editor):
   - Create tables: projects, project_members, entries, evidence_files, audit_logs
   - Enable RLS on all tables
   - Policies:
     - projects: owner can do everything; members read if permitted
     - project_members: only owner can manage; viewers read
     - entries: read/write only for members; owner shortcut for all
     - evidence_files: read for members; write for owner/editor
   - Storage:
     - Create bucket “evidence”
     - Storage policies: allow access to files under a path schema like evidence/{project_id}/...
4. Create SECURITY DEFINER functions:
   - create_project(owner_id, name, description)
   - add_member(project_id, user_id, role)
   - These avoid recursive policy evaluation while preserving security.

Policy philosophy:
- Always check auth.uid() membership
- Avoid recursive queries in policies (no policy chaining)
- Provide owner “bypass” policy for safety (but scoped)

